    &lt;p&gt;&lt;span/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;div&gt;
        There are various possibilities to position images in a note. You can either pull a image to the left or right of the note in a free-floating or fixed format. 
       &lt;span style=""&gt;This is a sample note which uses the tag &lt;/span&gt; 
       &lt;strong style=""&gt;clb-image-lightbox.&lt;/strong&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        The lightbox image strategy takes the pictures in your note and converts them to thumbnail images on your web page. When clicking on the image on the website all &amp;ldquo;lightbox&amp;rdquo; popup will be opened which shows the picture in full quality. 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        You find the image handling documentation on the 
       &lt;a href="https://curation.cloudburo.net/2015/05/14/feature-picture-handling-in-evernote-notes.html" rel="nofollow"&gt;Cloudburo Curation Platform documentation site&lt;/a&gt;. 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
